# Next.js

> Full-stack React framework with hybrid rendering, file-based routing, and built-in optimizations for production applications.

---

## Overview

Next.js is a React framework that provides:
- **Hybrid Rendering**: SSR, SSG, ISR, and CSR in one app
- **File-Based Routing**: App Router with layouts and nested routes
- **API Routes**: Backend endpoints alongside frontend
- **Built-in Optimizations**: Image, font, and script optimization
- **Zero Config**: Works out of the box with sensible defaults

---

## Why Next.js

| Feature | Benefit |
|---------|---------|
| Server Components | Smaller bundles, faster loads |
| App Router | Nested layouts, parallel routes |
| Built-in API | Full-stack in one codebase |
| Image Optimization | Automatic WebP, lazy loading |
| Edge Runtime | Deploy globally with low latency |

